   <abstract>Richard "Uncle Dick" Payne (1813-1885) sold water to Knoxvillians from his two-wheeled cart from 1845 until his death in 1885. He was an extremely popular merchant and is generally recognized as Knoxville's first "water works." Payne Street (in the Reservoir Hill area) is named in his honor.</abstract>
